I was expecting the shadow to do something as a shadow, and was a bit disappointed when it didn't. If you're not attached to the  part of your concept, a suggestion: the shadow remains a shadow, and attacks the shadow of the person who committed the crime, without the person suffering any injuries, or even feeling anything. The person's shadow will become out of sync with the person, looking and acting as if the person had suffered the injuries:

If the shadow suffered a leg injury, it will limp even though the person doesn't. If the injury is minor enough, the limp will eventually go away.
If the shadow had a finger cut off, the person's finger will be permanently shadow-less.
If the shadow was killed, the person will permanently have no shadow whatsoever.






